{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/bone-soft-tissue-sarcoma-recognition-referral/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"7c763a93-7e4c-5cd8-bcd6-5b896bfbba34","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 117b3299-b391-4577-af5c-a7f20187a3ab --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 117b3299-b391-4577-af5c-a7f20187a3ab -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 1820ab58-247a-44d1-afd2-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field 8f937c20-63bb-413a-af47-a7f20187a3ab --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 8f937c20-63bb-413a-af47-a7f20187a3ab --><!-- begin field 8d0f439d-2b7a-4221-807d-a7f20187a3ab --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 8d0f439d-2b7a-4221-807d-a7f20187a3ab --><!-- begin field 9ef3acb0-d0d8-4fc7-ae86-a7f20187a3ab --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 9ef3acb0-d0d8-4fc7-ae86-a7f20187a3ab --><!-- begin field d8f32502-ca55-4808-890f-a7f20187a3ab --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field d8f32502-ca55-4808-890f-a7f20187a3ab --><!-- begin field effb190d-ff94-4a1f-b7c0-a7f20187a3ab --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field effb190d-ff94-4a1f-b7c0-a7f20187a3ab --><!-- begin field 9b713c47-3df4-4506-bf1c-a7f20187a3ab --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 9b713c47-3df4-4506-bf1c-a7f20187a3ab --><!-- end item 1820ab58-247a-44d1-afd2-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"e4747ecc-d17a-5e2c-bd0c-69fc109a74f5","topicId":"6f65762b-a612-4ce9-80e5-ee8cb24f6dde","topicName":"Bone and soft tissue sarcoma - recognition and referral","slug":"bone-soft-tissue-sarcoma-recognition-referral","lastRevised":"Last revised in August 2020","chapters":[{"id":"edf8fdb6-68e6-5dac-916a-206d3893e4b8","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"0b6c5a9d-30a1-51f3-b16c-afbf78f00757","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"f18ae9ed-24b3-5a8f-b9fa-aabc10e5ced7","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"25f4d7d5-200e-50b1-b791-8478134bfee4","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"cee3f7fc-90f5-5bab-8b99-9ad854a538e7","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"69a11364-50c2-5893-ba48-bfc291fd9678","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"5941fcea-4bbf-5dbd-9c8b-4fffe5ff513c","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"82675336-6e84-5f8b-8ae2-b134dad3713d","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome meas